author: Andrew Beaton
title: Kirk Cousins Is Headed to Minnesota. What That Means for the Rest of the NFL
text:
Two months ago, Case Keenum led the Minnesota Vikings to the NFC Championship game on one of the most iconic plays in NFL history.
To understand how long ago that feels, this is what has transpired during the start of NFL free agency: Kirk Cousins is now Minnesotaâ€™s quarterback. Keenum is headed to the Denver Broncos. And the debris from a flurry of quarterback moves is still settling across the league.
